meta {
  name: Preview Agent Claim (POST /v1/agents/claim-preview)
  type: http
  seq: 106
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/v1/agents/claim-preview
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{sessionToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "userCode": "{{userCode}}"
  }
}

vars:pre-request {
  baseUrl: http://localhost:8080
}

docs {
  # POST /v1/agents/claim-preview

  Look up what confirming a claim-ceremony `user_code` would grant, so the wallet can show the
  agent's registration type, issuer/subject, and the exact scope list *before* the biometric
  approval gate (informed consent). Owner-authenticated (wallet session token or full-access
  access token); authorization mirrors `POST /agent/identity/claim/confirm`.

  Every failure shape — unknown code, expired attempt, a registration bound to a different
  account, already claimed/revoked — is a uniform 404. Shares the confirm endpoint's per-IP
  rate-limit budget (same 6-digit-code guessing surface).

  ## Response (200)

  ```json
  {
    "registrationId": "reg_...",
    "registrationType": "service_auth",
    "scopes": ["repo:app.bsky.feed.post?action=create", "blob:image/*"],
    "userCodeExpiresAt": "2026-01-01T00:10:00.000Z"
  }
  ```

  `issuer`/`subject` appear for `identity_assertion` registrations. `scopes` is the operator's
  current granted-scope profile — canonicalized exactly as confirmation will store it.
}
